<i>bound noun</i>: 정 [정] <i>noun</i>: 환 [환], 약 [약], 알약 [알략] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>bound noun</i><br>
<dt>정 [정]</dt><br>
<dd>capsule; pill</dd><br>
<dd>알약을 세는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun used to count tablet medicine.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>환 [환]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pill</dd><br>
<dd>한약재를 가루로 만들어 반죽해 작고 둥글게 빚은 약.</dd><br>
<dd>A small, round type of herbal medicine, formulated by making medicinal herb powders and kneading them.</dd><br>
<dd>2. pill</dd><br>
<dd>한약재를 가루로 만들어 반죽해 작고 둥글게 빚은 약의 개수를 세는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>A unit for counting the number of small, round pieces of medicine, formulated by making medicinal herb powders and kneading them.</dd><br>
<dt>약 [약]</dt><br>
<dd>1. medicine; medication; pill; drug</dd><br>
<dd>병이나 상처 등을 낫게 하거나 예방하기 위하여 먹거나 바르거나 주사하는 물질.</dd><br>
<dd>A substance orally administered, applied or injected to treat or prevent an illness, wound, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. insecticide; pesticide</dd><br>
<dd>해로운 벌레나 동식물을 없애는 데 사용하는 물질.</dd><br>
<dd>A substance that is used to get rid of harmful insects, animals or plants.</dd><br>
<dd>3. polish</dd><br>
<dd>물건에 윤기를 내기 위하여 바르는 물질.</dd><br>
<dd>A substance that is applied to an item to make it look shiny.</dd><br>
<dd>4. drug</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 마약이나 술.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A narcotic drug or alcoholic beverage.</dd><br>
<dd>5. battery</dd><br>
<dd>카메라, 라디오, 손전등 등에 쓰는, 전기를 일으키는 작은 물건.</dd><br>
<dd>A small item that produces an electric current and is used to power cameras, radios, lanterns, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>6. blessing; help; cure</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 몸이나 마음에 이롭거나 도움이 되는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) Something that is beneficial or helpful to the body or mind.</dd><br>
<dt>알약 [알략]</dt><br>
<dd>pill; tablet</dd><br>
<dd>가루약을 뭉쳐서 눌러 작고 둥글게 만든 약.</dd><br>
<dd>A small, round type of medicine, made by clumping and pressing powder medicine.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>